+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Mp2Am7nJ4vk5x8RG4RiMs9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01S2jhyeESQkQJk4utRsPLMu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-time-tracker.md","content":"# CLI Time Tracker Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a TypeScript time-tracking library with persistence, querying, and summary features.\n\n**Architecture:** Single-module library with a `TimeTracker` class that manages time entries in memory and persists them to a JSON file. Entries are stored as an array of `{task, start, end?}` objects. The class tracks the currently running timer and provides methods for start/stop/query/summarize.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16 modules), Node.js built-in `fs` and `path` modules, Vitest for testing.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Install dependencies\n\n**Step 1: Install npm packages**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace && npm install`\nExpected: All devDependencies installed successfully.\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Create core types and data model\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the types file**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface TimeEntry {\n  task: string;\n  start: string; // ISO 8601\n  end: string | null; // ISO 8601 or null if running\n}\n\nexport interface TimeSummary {\n  [task: string]: number; // milliseconds\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify build**\n\nRun: `npm run build`\nExpected: PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Create the TimeTracker class with start/stop\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tracker.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Implement the TimeTracker class**\n\nThe class should:\n- Accept a `filePath` in constructor\n- Load existing entries from the JSON file on construction (async `init()` or `load()`)\n- `start(task: string)` — validate non-empty name, stop running timer if any, add new entry\n- `stop()` — find running entry, set its end time, throw if nothing running\n- `getEntries()` — return all entries\n- `getEntriesByDateRange(start: Date, end: Date)` — filter entries\n- `getSummary()` — aggregate time per task name\n- Auto-persist to JSON file after mutations\n- Auto-create file and parent directories if they don't exist\n\n**Step 2: Verify build**\n\nRun: `npm run build`\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Create public API in index.ts\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Export public API**\n\n```typescript\nexport { TimeTracker } from './tracker.js';\nexport { TimeEntry, TimeSummary } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify build and lint**\n\nRun: `npm run build && npm run lint`\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Write tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tracker.test.ts`\n\nCover:\n- Start a timer, verify entry created\n- Stop a timer, verify end time set\n- Start with empty name throws\n- Stop when nothing running throws\n- Auto-stop previous timer when starting new one\n- Persistence: create tracker, add entries, create new tracker with same file, verify entries loaded\n- Date range filtering\n- Summary aggregation (multiple entries for same task)\n- Running tasks use current time in summary\n- Unicode/emoji task names\n- Auto-create directories for file path\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Final verification\n\nRun: `npm run build && npm run lint && npm test`\nAll must pass.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":119,"cache_read_input_tokens":20576,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":119},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c70c30f4-bc3f-4870-b646-5ebb699bb6a6","uuid":"3ae214d7-dab5-4a7a-bb90-d9b9520798f6"}
